<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Creophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Creophilus erythrocephalus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrocephalus">Creophilus erythrocephalus (Fabricius, 1775)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Taxon discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Creophilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Creophilus erythrocephalus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrocephalus">Creophilus erythrocephalus</taxonomicName>
is recorded from New Guinea, Australia, Lord Howe Island, New Caledonia, Tonga, Society Islands (French Polynesia), Hawaii, Easter Island, and finally Chile, where it is apparently introduced (
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, A" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="203 - 378" title="Faune analytique des Coleopteres de la Nouvelle-Caledonie." volume="22" year="1903">Fauvel 1903</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Clarke, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="723 - 812" title="Testing the phylogenetic utility of morphological character systems, with a revision of Creophilus Leach (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2011.00725.x" volume="163" year="2011">Clarke 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The species is found in open or disturbed habitats, often on dung and carrion; also can be attracted by light (
<bibRefCitation author="Clarke, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="723 - 812" title="Testing the phylogenetic utility of morphological character systems, with a revision of Creophilus Leach (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2011.00725.x" volume="163" year="2011">Clarke 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It was first reported from LHI by 
<bibRefCitation author="Olliff, A" editor="Ramsey, E" journalOrPublisher="Charles Potter, Government Printer, Sydney" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" title="The Insect Fauna of Lord Howe Island." url="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1967.2.1889.482" volumeTitle="Lord Howe Island. Its Zoology, Geology, and physical characters" year="1889">Olliff (1889)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
